The concept of the Game “Election ka Baazigar” is about skillfully calculating the seats of each Political Party for each State (or Zone as the case may be) for Elections 2023 in the States of Madhya Pradesh, Chhattisgarh, Rajasthan, Telangana & Mizoram (cumulatively referred to as “Election States”) and win prizes, during the Game Play Period 21st Nov'23 to 1st Dec'23 [“Event”].
Participant acknowledges that the below mentioned Terms generally apply to the Gaming Events conducted by ACPL, however in the event specific terms and conditions are published/ displayed, the participants are advised to refer to such specific terms and conditions which shall be binding. The Gaming Event will be hosted on various platforms/mediums of ACPL and also on ABP Live App (App available on Google Play Store as well as on iOS Store) and abplive.com during the gaming event time period. Any person ("User") accessing such medium (“ACPL platform”) for participating in the various contests shall be bound by these Terms, and all other rules, regulations and terms of use referred to herein or provided by ACPL in relation to any of its Event.
1.The Participant is advised to research and be well informed about the history of the Election States, the Election Results in the past, the list of Assemblies that were constituted, various existing and past controversies and all such things as may be necessary to participate in this game of skill and in order to have an edge in becoming a winner. The Participant is advised to avoid guesswork and to play skillfully. The Participant may peruse the TIPS section of the game to avail help in playing the game skillfully. 2.The Participant shall make seat predictions of different political parties in 5 Election States. As a second step, for each State you are required to select the number of seats which are likely to be won by your chosen Party. As a final step, you are required to submit your entry and before which you are permitted to edit as many times as required until such date to be decided as a ‘Cut-off date’ at the sole discretion of ACPL. In order to aid and assist you and in order to facilitate as a lifeline, we shall be making available to you the data of past Elections. 3.Winner selection and the Rules for User Participation: (i) Each Participant shall be able to submit predictions for only one time for each State; (ii) Each participant shall be able to edit the seat count prediction only till 1st Dec'23 midnight and the last submitted prediction shall be submitted for the Event; (iii) The winner shall be announced based on how closely the predictions have been made viz-a-viz actual seat count; (iv) The results will be announced on/after 5th Dec'23; (v) The winners shall be reached out on call/text and in case the winners don't respond within 7 days of the announcement, the prize shall automatically be given to the next best in each State; (vi) In the event of a draw in any State prediction, ACPL shall assess the accuracy of predictions made in the other States. The winner of that State shall be determined based on the closest prediction in the other States. If any Participant has not attempted predictions for other States, the prize shall be awarded to the Participant who has at least made an attempt; (vii) There shall be only 1 winner for each State; (viii) This skill based gaming Event does not involve any financial transaction. (. 4.Prize Distribution: (i) Mobile numbers of the Winners shall be published in the RANK section of the Game on/after 5th December 2023; (ii) Winners shall be rewarded GOQii Weighing scales (iv) Participants shall be asked to furnish valid KYC documentation i.e., Address proof - Aadhar card, PAN copy. Additional KYC documents may be requested at ACPL’s sole discretion. Non-compliance will lead to disqualification; (v) to claim the prize, the Winners shall have to send their respective valid ID proofs. The Winners shall be given 48 hours to send the ID proof failing which he or she shall be construed as disqualified; (vi) Three (3) attempts shall be made to contact Winners. Records for the same shall not be shared with the Winners. In the event the Participants cannot be contacted then the prizes, if any, shall be awarded to the next eligible Participant; (vii) The prizes shall be delivered to the Winners within 30 days from the date of intimation to the Winner. ACPL shall not be liable if the prize is not delivered due to any technical or unforeseen reason or in the event the prize gets damaged by a courier/in transit, ACPL shall not be liable in any manner whatsoever to courier another prize; (viii) In the event an advertised prize is not available, ACPL reserves the right to offer an alternative prize of equal or greater value at its sole discretion; (ix) Any correspondence from ACPL to the Participants shall be directed by phone call and/or SMS as provided by the Participant; (x) The decision of ACPL will be final and binding. No communication shall be entered into with any person in relation to any decision of the process; (xi) ACPL is entitled to verify the Participants by themselves o